The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 January is 181,007 (20,862.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 January, there were 8,480 new confirmed cases (977.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 January, there were 7,605 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 12% (875 extra cases).
